  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - BARD</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'> BARD RACE AND CLASS COMBO'S</font> - <small>Hova, Luclin</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>
<p>  First off I would like to start by saying there is no 'the best' race/class combo.  Look at this way if your big your easy to hit but hit hard, small your hard to hit but hit small also.
Here's a another thing that throws a kink in it, what dungeon past 20 can a big old
Ogre fit in with out a shaman, or a shrink potion. A lot of people say ogres, the best at the fighter and SK stat wise, but they never think of the field.  Guards grab
you by the knickers, druid use you for fertilizing treants, and you never get a kiss from that cute wood elf ).
I've found that ogres, gnomes, dwarfs anything that don't look like a human tend to get
shunted, a halfling KS you, 'dirty rotten hairy footed sonva b-----d', hehe, a wood elf KS
you, and you get the ' hmm Keno just KSed us again' (Keno is made up name, in RL probably a good guy), keep an eye on that.</p>
<p>  Anyway enough with that, now the best bard race is.</p>
<p>For me I liked the half elf, no need for wis and a half elf don't have it so the starting str and dex is abit higher because of it, Dex is your ability to play
instruments and have rhythm, if you don't have that ability you might as well not play a bard, next is your charisma, think about a butch ugly troll singing a song
you going to follow it, next str mainly in my life the ability to pack more
armour and money which = better armour = better chance of making it out of a dungeon
or fight alive or at least a shorter run to your corpse depending on which way you
went ). Half elf bard good str, good dex, nice agi, good charisma, moves abit slower than human, has
infra (good for running down a tunnel naked), rated 2nd as best lookers I think ).&nbsp;</p>
<p>Wood elf can use small armour, nice for weight allowance since you have a bit lower str, the agi is higher than others,
charisma is I think higher, then the other 2 races, and your dex is the best or at least
same with halfelfs, has infra, oh and rated 3rd best looker for males 1 for females.&nbsp;</p>
<p>  Humans, blind as a bat, levels faster than the other 2 even stats because they
don't get a race penalty (no they don't get a race xp bonus either, just the halflings), race wise
you can say a human is like the bard class 'jack of all trades master of none'  has to wear med
armour (heavier) like the half elf, and I think its 4 or 5th rank for looks which means less kisses from wood elf girls. As for places to start all races depending on good can chose any of the 3 cities, other than maybe the wood elf they I think are stuck with the tree house (cant remember the name).<br>
<br>
  As for leveling I think where and how has been said enough if not go check out another write up
they're all the same.  At level 1 you move good then level 6 comes along, you know student driver cars, where the instructor has a brake peddle on their side well I think
Verant really layed a big patch of rubber because I swear you kill something it don't
move hehe, I once heard bard get a solo penalty by the sounds of it, its not true, but the rumor has some truth it tells
you what your suppose to be doing.<br>
<br>
  Anyway think about it remember its a hybrid class, In short ever drive a mail truck
that's what a hybrid feels like.  Also there's no clear winner same thing with all the other classes.  Its what
you want or what reflects your RL personally a dark elf rouge who never steals, or a nice wood elf who will stab
you in the back first chance they get.  Stat wise you look good but try fitting through a normal sized door let alone the actual 6 foot x 6 foot hallway,
literally I've got my ogres head stuck on the roof running out of CT, only reason I squeezed through was a big lizard kicking my ass out the door ).<br>
<br>
And on a personal note don't beg, only time I do is when I'm trying to out run a bigger creature and the group
I'm running to is healthy and looking for that type of creature.  Other than that
I've always made my own stuff or paid for sows binds any kind of spell, unless its a run by sowing.<br>
<br>
  Good luck on which ever race/class you decide to play, you'll need it.</p>
</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'>&nbsp;</td></tr>
